1
00:01:57,110 --> 00:02:01,990
=Yummy Yummy Yummy=

2
00:02:02,020 --> 00:02:04,900
=Episode 7=

3
00:02:08,660 --> 00:02:11,460
(Good night)

4
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:19,900
(Good night)

5
00:02:20,580 --> 00:02:22,510
We're finally going back.

6
00:02:22,740 --> 00:02:24,710
Somehow,
I feel a bit reluctant to leave.

7
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:25,690
Indeed.

8
00:02:25,690 --> 00:02:26,810
I've almost gotten used

9
00:02:26,810 --> 00:02:28,710
to living in Yong'an.

10
00:02:28,930 --> 00:02:29,780
Once I'm back,

11
00:02:29,780 --> 00:02:31,350
I'll surely miss the ancestor.

12
00:02:31,660 --> 00:02:32,600
Here it comes!

13
00:02:38,570 --> 00:02:39,760
Smells amazing.

14
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:45,440
The moon is full now.

15
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:47,250
As long as our ancestor here is won over

16
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:49,690
by this Spring Water Lamb,

17
00:02:49,690 --> 00:02:50,790
we can go back.

18
00:02:53,130 --> 00:02:54,160
He's coming.

19
00:02:55,940 --> 00:02:56,880
Hurry.

20
00:03:02,770 --> 00:03:04,160
Welcome, Vice Prefect.

21
00:03:09,060 --> 00:03:10,180
I thought

22
00:03:10,180 --> 00:03:11,440
it was just an ordinary meal.

23
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:13,000
It's so lavish.

24
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:15,380
You've even made so many lanterns.

25
00:03:15,380 --> 00:03:16,740
It has to be special
because you're here.

26
00:03:16,740 --> 00:03:17,650
- Yes.
- Ancestor...

27
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:19,290
Vice Prefect, please sit down.

28
00:03:21,980 --> 00:03:23,340
- Sit.
- Sit here.

29
00:03:23,340 --> 00:03:24,260
Everyone sit.

30
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:26,780
Liu Chang,

31
00:03:26,780 --> 00:03:27,780
sit. Here.

32
00:03:27,780 --> 00:03:28,660
- I...
- Together.

33
00:03:28,660 --> 00:03:29,860
Uncle Liu Chang, hurry and sit.

34
00:03:29,860 --> 00:03:31,180
Please sit, Mr. Liu.

35
00:03:31,340 --> 00:03:32,260
Okay.

36
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:34,780
Vice Prefect, you must try

37
00:03:34,780 --> 00:03:35,780
this Spring Water Lamb

38
00:03:35,780 --> 00:03:37,900
we specially made for you.

39
00:03:38,140 --> 00:03:39,060
Please.

40
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:47,780
Well...

41
00:03:48,060 --> 00:03:49,420
I won't stand on ceremony then.

42
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:10,940
Delicious.

43
00:04:23,820 --> 00:04:24,740
Calm down!

44
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:32,500
Now that Lady Shen faces
no further worries.

45
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:35,220
Young Master, you can propose

46
00:04:35,770 --> 00:04:37,170
dissolving the engagement, right?

47
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,500
Since everyone is here,

48
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:43,020
I have a matter

49
00:04:43,020 --> 00:04:44,380
I wish to discuss with you all.

50
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:45,660
What a coincidence.

51
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:47,140
We also have some things

52
00:04:47,140 --> 00:04:48,540
to tell you.

53
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,370
Vice Prefect, you speak first.

54
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:53,540
What I have to say isn't urgent.

55
00:04:53,730 --> 00:04:55,420
Please, Uncle, you go first.

56
00:04:55,660 --> 00:04:56,620
No, no!

57
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:58,340
You speak first.

58
00:04:58,340 --> 00:04:59,700
Uncle, you should speak first.

59
00:04:59,700 --> 00:05:01,260
Vice Prefect, you should speak first.

60
00:05:01,260 --> 00:05:02,500
Then Auntie should speak.

61
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:07,940
I'll speak then.

62
00:05:07,940 --> 00:05:10,260
Vice Prefect, we've prepared
a farewell gift for you.

63
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:13,060
Farewell...?

64
00:05:18,580 --> 00:05:20,180
This is clothing we specially made.

65
00:05:20,180 --> 00:05:21,460
We designed the pattern ourselves

66
00:05:21,460 --> 00:05:22,280
and had it made.

67
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:24,540
We hope you will always
have splendid robes to wear.

68
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:26,380
Yes, Vice Prefect.

69
00:05:26,740 --> 00:05:27,740
We also made

70
00:05:27,740 --> 00:05:28,980
these lanterns especially.

71
00:05:28,980 --> 00:05:31,660
We hope they can illuminate your future.

72
00:05:31,860 --> 00:05:33,300
Right! Vice Prefect,

73
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:34,860
I also have a gift for you.

74
00:05:35,820 --> 00:05:37,900
(Our Family)
This is a family portrait I drew myself.

75
00:05:37,900 --> 00:05:39,460
And I drew you right in the center.

76
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:42,460
Center?

77
00:05:43,340 --> 00:05:44,260
I guess

78
00:05:45,020 --> 00:05:46,980
that means I've been stuffed

79
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:48,220
into this spot.

80
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:50,940
What it means is

81
00:05:50,940 --> 00:05:52,620
you hold the most important position

82
00:05:52,620 --> 00:05:54,500
in our family's hearts.

83
00:05:56,460 --> 00:05:58,180
(Our Family)

84
00:06:07,380 --> 00:06:08,300
Thank you.

85
00:06:11,380 --> 00:06:12,300
But

86
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:14,020
just now, you said this was

87
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:15,300
a "farewell gift"?

88
00:06:15,860 --> 00:06:16,780
Yes.

89
00:06:17,140 --> 00:06:18,660
It's like this, Vice Prefect.

90
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:19,900
We've been imposing on you here

91
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:21,780
for quite some time now.

92
00:06:22,380 --> 00:06:24,100
We should be returning to our hometown.

93
00:06:24,340 --> 00:06:26,260
So we prepared

94
00:06:26,420 --> 00:06:27,420
some gifts for you.

95
00:06:27,420 --> 00:06:29,260
They're all small items we made by hand.

96
00:06:29,980 --> 00:06:31,500
We also hope your life in the future

97
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:32,780
will be more comfortable.

98
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:35,140
Today, we also tidied up your courtyard

99
00:06:35,140 --> 00:06:36,860
and the inside of the house.

100
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:38,940
Hope you don't mind.

101
00:06:39,710 --> 00:06:40,740
Vice Prefect,

102
00:06:41,420 --> 00:06:42,380
all this time,

103
00:06:42,900 --> 00:06:44,380
we've truly troubled you.

104
00:06:44,740 --> 00:06:46,380
Our whole family is deeply grateful.

105
00:06:47,340 --> 00:06:48,260
We should toast

106
00:06:48,780 --> 00:06:49,700
this cup to you.

107
00:06:50,540 --> 00:06:51,380
- Here.
- Here.

108
00:06:51,380 --> 00:06:52,300
Here.

109
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:53,220
Toast to Vice Prefect.

110
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:07,380
Well...

111
00:07:07,380 --> 00:07:08,900
Everyone, stop standing up.

112
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:10,340
- Hurry and eat!
- Come here.

113
00:07:10,340 --> 00:07:11,380
Sit!

114
00:07:11,380 --> 00:07:12,660
Come and sit. Eat!

115
00:07:12,660 --> 00:07:13,720
- Help yourself.
- Eat quickly.

116
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,100
- Yangyang, here.
- Here.

117
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:20,620
Thank you, Uncle.

118
00:07:20,980 --> 00:07:21,860
Earlier, you said

119
00:07:21,860 --> 00:07:23,180
you had something to tell us.

120
00:07:23,380 --> 00:07:24,300
What was it?

121
00:07:26,740 --> 00:07:27,660
Minor matters.

122
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:29,690
Perhaps not worth mentioning.

123
00:07:30,980 --> 00:07:31,980
Then have some food.

124
00:07:32,540 --> 00:07:33,460
Here.

125
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:35,980
Mr. Liu, try this.

126
00:07:35,980 --> 00:07:36,900
Thank you, Auntie.

127
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:39,660
This is the recipe for rice tofu.

128
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:40,820
We'll leave it with you.

129
00:07:40,820 --> 00:07:41,700
Keep it.

130
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:43,200
After we leave,
don't forget to eat properly.

131
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:44,300
Don't be busy with official duties

132
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:45,700
and dryly gnaw
on steamed buns every day.

133
00:07:49,860 --> 00:07:53,940
(Rice Tofu Recipe)

134
00:08:01,300 --> 00:08:02,180
Auntie,

135
00:08:02,180 --> 00:08:04,420
these lanterns swaying
look just like fireflies.

136
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:08,140
What are...

137
00:08:08,620 --> 00:08:09,540
fireflies?

138
00:08:10,820 --> 00:08:11,700
They're

139
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:12,620
glowworms.

140
00:08:13,940 --> 00:08:14,860
Glowworms!

141
00:08:16,780 --> 00:08:17,700
Yangyang,

142
00:08:17,980 --> 00:08:19,620
I know a place to see fireflies.

143
00:08:19,620 --> 00:08:20,540
Want to go?

144
00:08:20,820 --> 00:08:21,700
Want to!

145
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:22,620
Where is it?

146
00:08:23,180 --> 00:08:24,260
Then after dinner, I'll take you.

147
00:08:24,460 --> 00:08:25,300
Okay!

148
00:08:25,300 --> 00:08:26,380
Then it'll be troublesome for you

149
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:27,860
to look after Yangyang for me later.

150
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:30,980
Let's go together.

151
00:08:33,740 --> 00:08:34,980
But if we go out now,

152
00:08:34,980 --> 00:08:36,420
isn't that violating the curfew?

153
00:08:36,980 --> 00:08:37,880
We'll go out the back gate.

154
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:39,170
Without going to Vermilion Bird Avenue,

155
00:08:39,180 --> 00:08:40,660
we can avoid the patrols.

156
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:43,680
The fireflies by the Cang River
are Yong'an's most famous night view.

157
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:45,820
You will be leaving soon.

158
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:46,980
If you miss it this time,

159
00:08:47,780 --> 00:08:49,100
it might be hard to have another chance.

160
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,020
Here. Eat first.

161
00:08:58,020 --> 00:08:59,130
Eat your fill and then we'll talk.

162
00:09:07,620 --> 00:09:09,220
So beautiful.

163
00:09:09,220 --> 00:09:10,340
So many.

164
00:09:10,980 --> 00:09:12,100
Uncle Vice Prefect,

165
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:12,920
when I go back,

166
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:13,890
whenever I see fireflies,

167
00:09:13,890 --> 00:09:15,260
I'll definitely remember you.

168
00:09:15,260 --> 00:09:16,540
What's Uncle Vice Prefect?

169
00:09:16,540 --> 00:09:17,620
Don't call him that.

170
00:09:18,780 --> 00:09:19,700
It's alright.

171
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:40,540
Auntie, I caught a firefly!

172
00:09:41,780 --> 00:09:43,220
Yangyang, don't catch them.

173
00:09:43,220 --> 00:09:45,340
Fireflies will die within a day
if you trap them.

174
00:09:45,340 --> 00:09:47,460
It's better to let them be free.

175
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:04,220
May you

176
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:06,420
be free, too.

177
00:10:07,740 --> 00:10:08,860
Freedom

178
00:10:09,540 --> 00:10:11,620
is my greatest wish in this life.

179
00:10:15,140 --> 00:10:16,220
To be honest,

180
00:10:17,420 --> 00:10:18,580
when I first met you,

181
00:10:18,580 --> 00:10:19,820
I thought you were...

182
00:10:20,460 --> 00:10:21,620
I thought you were a high official.

183
00:10:22,540 --> 00:10:24,540
I thought you should be enshrined.

184
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:26,540
But after spending time together,

185
00:10:26,540 --> 00:10:28,540
I found you have a cold face
but a warm heart.

186
00:10:29,820 --> 00:10:31,860
Now I actually feel like

187
00:10:32,140 --> 00:10:33,260
you are a friend.

188
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:38,260
It's a pity
I'm just a passerby in Yong'an.

189
00:10:38,260 --> 00:10:39,740
I don't belong here.

190
00:10:39,940 --> 00:10:41,060
So I decided long ago

191
00:10:41,060 --> 00:10:42,660
not to make friends here.

192
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:50,220
What a coincidence.

193
00:10:50,980 --> 00:10:51,900
Me too.

194
00:10:59,380 --> 00:11:00,300
Then...

195
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:03,180
we are not friends.

196
00:11:04,570 --> 00:11:07,090
♪Red clay surrounds the hearth fire♪

197
00:11:07,090 --> 00:11:11,400
♪A season of yearning sows
a peck of lovesick beans♪

198
00:11:11,940 --> 00:11:14,810
♪Heart adds fierce flames,
chills melancholy♪

199
00:11:14,810 --> 00:11:20,510
♪Raising my gaze,
drunk towards white hair♪

200
00:11:24,580 --> 00:11:25,500
Auntie!

201
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:26,820
Auntie, look at the fireflies.

202
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:28,500
So beautiful.

203
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:32,080
♪Awake or mad, that's all for later♪

204
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:34,690
♪Could it be, without schemes♪

205
00:11:34,690 --> 00:11:37,100
♪Without longing, without turning back♪

206
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:41,540
♪Only thinking of today,
not seeking results♪

207
00:11:41,830 --> 00:11:45,950
♪With a beginning and an end♪

208
00:12:00,340 --> 00:12:01,260
Mr. Liu,

209
00:12:01,620 --> 00:12:02,540
I have a major matter,

210
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:04,820
even a lifelong matter,

211
00:12:04,820 --> 00:12:05,740
that I'd like to ask

212
00:12:05,740 --> 00:12:06,660
for your help with.

213
00:12:06,940 --> 00:12:07,860
Alright.

214
00:12:08,340 --> 00:12:09,260
So,

215
00:12:09,580 --> 00:12:10,820
after that poetry gathering,

216
00:12:11,180 --> 00:12:12,220
I received

217
00:12:12,460 --> 00:12:14,300
quite a few poetic letters
from noble ladies of Yong'an.

218
00:12:14,540 --> 00:12:15,940
My usual focus is

219
00:12:15,940 --> 00:12:17,340
deciphering oracle bone scripts.

220
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:19,060
I'm not very knowledgeable

221
00:12:19,060 --> 00:12:20,220
about poetry and such things.

222
00:12:20,540 --> 00:12:21,900
So I'd like to ask you

223
00:12:22,340 --> 00:12:23,780
to help me parse them.

224
00:12:23,980 --> 00:12:25,180
- Here.
- I'll just...

225
00:12:25,420 --> 00:12:26,340
take a look.

226
00:12:27,700 --> 00:12:29,090
(Kneeling down; Reading book;
Eat well; Miss you always)

227
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:29,980
This one

228
00:12:29,980 --> 00:12:31,460
praises

229
00:12:31,820 --> 00:12:32,860
your outstanding talent

230
00:12:32,860 --> 00:12:34,780
and that day's "battle of wits".

231
00:12:37,260 --> 00:12:39,140
This one praises you

232
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:40,220
as suave, handsome,

233
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:41,380
and dashing.

234
00:12:41,940 --> 00:12:42,860
Is that so?

235
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:45,700
What?

236
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:46,660
Handsome and dashing?

237
00:12:46,660 --> 00:12:47,740
This one is even more impressive.

238
00:12:47,940 --> 00:12:49,060
This young lady

239
00:12:49,260 --> 00:12:51,340
has a secret affection for you.

240
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:53,820
Here. Let me see.

241
00:12:54,660 --> 00:12:55,580
Give me one.

242
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:58,660
(Dreamed you were near;
Woke to you gone.)

243
00:12:58,900 --> 00:13:00,660
Couldn't they have been delivered
to the wrong place?

244
00:13:01,060 --> 00:13:02,400
This is too unbelievable.

245
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,540
If I'd known it would be like this,

246
00:13:03,540 --> 00:13:04,580
I should have made some comments

247
00:13:04,820 --> 00:13:06,860
at the poetry gathering, too.

248
00:13:06,860 --> 00:13:08,480
Maybe I could have
gotten some fans, too.

249
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:10,420
What are you stirring up trouble for?

250
00:13:10,420 --> 00:13:12,340
And so on.

251
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:15,060
Here's another one.

252
00:13:17,060 --> 00:13:19,140
What truly makes a confidante?

253
00:13:19,420 --> 00:13:21,220
What truly makes a beauty?

254
00:13:21,220 --> 00:13:22,140
Oh my.

255
00:13:24,980 --> 00:13:26,300
Didn't expect people here

256
00:13:26,540 --> 00:13:28,340
to have such taste.

257
00:13:28,340 --> 00:13:30,300
I'm actually a bit reluctant to leave.

258
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:32,130
I'll take this affection
with me when I leave.

259
00:13:32,940 --> 00:13:34,580
No matter how bad life gets later,

260
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:37,420
I'll rely on these

261
00:13:38,180 --> 00:13:40,020
to keep going strong.

262
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:44,900
Listen,

263
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:45,820
I...

264
00:13:46,940 --> 00:13:48,500
Where are the people?

265
00:13:48,780 --> 00:13:49,700
This...

266
00:13:50,180 --> 00:13:51,100
this...

267
00:13:51,620 --> 00:13:53,420
You simply don't understand me!

268
00:14:03,580 --> 00:14:04,980
According to the script I wrote,

269
00:14:05,460 --> 00:14:07,540
we were supposed to move our ancestor

270
00:14:07,540 --> 00:14:09,540
with a perfect bowl of Spring Water Lamb

271
00:14:09,540 --> 00:14:10,740
on a full moon night.

272
00:14:10,740 --> 00:14:11,980
Then we bathe in the moonlight,

273
00:14:12,340 --> 00:14:13,260
fall asleep,

274
00:14:13,460 --> 00:14:15,380
and wake up back in the modern era.

275
00:14:18,580 --> 00:14:20,380
You know, the money we earned here

276
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:23,260
is enough for us
to live on for years back home.

277
00:14:24,260 --> 00:14:25,260
Honestly,

278
00:14:25,260 --> 00:14:27,100
I feel earning money in ancient times

279
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:28,980
was so much easier
than in the modern era.

280
00:14:29,340 --> 00:14:31,660
I'm actually reluctant to leave Yong'an.

281
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:32,820
Yeah.

282
00:14:33,580 --> 00:14:35,220
Although you can't
play video games here,

283
00:14:35,220 --> 00:14:36,890
and there aren't
many modern conveniences,

284
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:38,620
the money is easy to make here.

285
00:14:39,060 --> 00:14:40,180
Mom, it'll be even harder

286
00:14:40,180 --> 00:14:41,180
for someone like me

287
00:14:41,580 --> 00:14:43,060
to find a job back in the modern era.

288
00:14:43,060 --> 00:14:44,920
And our family restaurant
isn't doing well now.

289
00:14:46,220 --> 00:14:47,060
Keep looking at me.

290
00:14:47,060 --> 00:14:48,180
It's still going under.

291
00:14:48,420 --> 00:14:49,740
- Hey!
- You know, here,

292
00:14:49,740 --> 00:14:51,430
if we just make a little bit
of modern-style food,

293
00:14:51,460 --> 00:14:53,580
the money comes whooshing in.

294
00:14:53,580 --> 00:14:55,220
And I could have so many fans.

295
00:14:55,540 --> 00:14:56,740
Isn't that great?

296
00:14:57,580 --> 00:14:59,500
None of what you say is important.

297
00:14:59,780 --> 00:15:01,020
I heard that next year,

298
00:15:01,020 --> 00:15:02,180
Yong'an will host

299
00:15:02,180 --> 00:15:03,660
the first Culinary Master Competition.

300
00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:05,660
If we really stay until then,

301
00:15:05,900 --> 00:15:07,460
perhaps I could win us

302
00:15:07,460 --> 00:15:08,460
a ranking.

303
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:10,740
If I really could get a ranking,

304
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:13,140
I would have a bunch of fans, too.

305
00:15:13,140 --> 00:15:14,220
If I became popular,

306
00:15:14,220 --> 00:15:16,420
my fans would definitely
be more than yours.

307
00:15:16,580 --> 00:15:17,460
Enough.

308
00:15:17,460 --> 00:15:18,620
Enough with you.

309
00:15:19,060 --> 00:15:21,380
How capable you are, don't I know?

310
00:15:21,940 --> 00:15:23,220
Endless nonsense.

311
00:15:23,660 --> 00:15:24,980
Culinary Master?

312
00:15:25,380 --> 00:15:27,300
Actually, I think
what Dad said isn't bad.

313
00:15:27,300 --> 00:15:28,540
Look at Dad's presence.

314
00:15:28,540 --> 00:15:29,820
With a little grooming,

315
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,420
he's an absolute
middle-aged idol material.

316
00:15:31,420 --> 00:15:32,300
Right, Dad?

317
00:15:33,380 --> 00:15:34,300
Dad!

318
00:15:36,860 --> 00:15:37,820
Actually,

319
00:15:37,980 --> 00:15:39,460
I also like Yong'an.

320
00:15:39,460 --> 00:15:41,220
Because the ancestor plays with me.

321
00:15:43,180 --> 00:15:44,100
So,

322
00:15:45,460 --> 00:15:47,500
why don't we just not go back?

323
00:15:52,020 --> 00:15:54,460
No, I... I was just saying it casually.

324
00:15:54,460 --> 00:15:56,220
No other meaning.

325
00:15:58,340 --> 00:15:59,660
Actually,

326
00:16:00,580 --> 00:16:01,900
it might not be impossible.

327
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,220
Actually,

328
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:06,100
it has some logic.

329
00:16:07,380 --> 00:16:08,300
But

330
00:16:08,540 --> 00:16:11,460
Auntie told the ancestor
a monumental lie.

331
00:16:11,620 --> 00:16:13,940
What if he finds out?

332
00:16:20,300 --> 00:16:21,460
Time is almost up.

333
00:16:21,460 --> 00:16:22,490
Stop all this wishful thinking.

334
00:16:22,490 --> 00:16:23,750
Let's all accept our fate and go back.

335
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:25,700
After all, we have so much gold.

336
00:16:25,700 --> 00:16:26,980
Life will get better.

337
00:16:27,780 --> 00:16:28,700
Fine.

338
00:16:28,900 --> 00:16:31,620
I'll go back carrying
the love from my fans.

339
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:40,820
Take it.

340
00:17:07,860 --> 00:17:11,020
(Our Family)

341
00:17:11,020 --> 00:17:12,940
You hold the most important position

342
00:17:12,940 --> 00:17:14,860
in our family's hearts.

343
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:23,600
(Remember to drink water. Eat on time)
After we leave, don't forget to eat.

344
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:24,700
Don't be busy with official duties

345
00:17:24,700 --> 00:17:26,060
and dryly gnaw
on steamed buns every day.

346
00:17:35,660 --> 00:17:42,100
(Yunshui Manor. Welcome Home)

347
00:17:44,220 --> 00:17:46,940
Finally back to a place
with wireless internet.

348
00:17:47,620 --> 00:17:51,100
And we need to find a place
that buys gold at a high price.

349
00:17:58,300 --> 00:17:59,380
Lady Shen.

350
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:10,540
Why am I still here?

351
00:18:10,820 --> 00:18:11,780
Lady Shen,

352
00:18:11,950 --> 00:18:13,580
last night,
everyone somehow got so drunk

353
00:18:13,580 --> 00:18:14,880
and fell asleep in the courtyard.

354
00:18:14,980 --> 00:18:17,420
Steward Liu worried you'd catch a chill
from drunkenness,

355
00:18:17,620 --> 00:18:18,820
so he quickly sent you all back

356
00:18:18,820 --> 00:18:19,940
to your respective rooms.

357
00:18:28,580 --> 00:18:29,940
Thinking from another angle,

358
00:18:30,780 --> 00:18:32,540
actually, from the very beginning,

359
00:18:32,860 --> 00:18:34,420
all the methods for going back

360
00:18:34,420 --> 00:18:36,140
were ones we thought up.

361
00:18:36,460 --> 00:18:37,700
And we tried them all.

362
00:18:38,420 --> 00:18:41,340
Since there's truly no way back now,

363
00:18:41,540 --> 00:18:42,940
doesn't it mean

364
00:18:43,380 --> 00:18:45,500
we can only face reality?

365
00:18:51,020 --> 00:18:52,340
Staying here

366
00:18:54,420 --> 00:18:56,260
might be quite good.

367
00:18:56,940 --> 00:18:58,260
Someone like me

368
00:18:58,260 --> 00:18:59,140
has nothing

369
00:18:59,140 --> 00:19:00,260
in the modern era.

370
00:19:00,260 --> 00:19:01,620
But here, in ancient times,

371
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:04,260
I really am quite popular.

372
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:06,500
And it seems that

373
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:08,220
our ancestor's character
isn't bad either.

374
00:19:08,780 --> 00:19:09,700
So,

375
00:19:12,260 --> 00:19:13,900
why don't we just really stay?

376
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:15,380
Open a small restaurant and enjoy

377
00:19:15,620 --> 00:19:17,460
the ancestral patronage
we don't have in the modern era.

378
00:19:17,660 --> 00:19:19,780
Maybe we'll end up
as the richest family.

379
00:19:20,300 --> 00:19:21,940
Shen Gongcai, what time is it!

380
00:19:21,940 --> 00:19:23,370
And you're still thinking about this?

381
00:19:23,370 --> 00:19:24,340
I'm not...

382
00:19:25,020 --> 00:19:25,940
Yeah.

383
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:27,420
What your sister said is right.

384
00:19:27,820 --> 00:19:29,140
Your relaxation mentality

385
00:19:29,140 --> 00:19:30,300
is definitely wrong.

386
00:19:30,620 --> 00:19:32,430
One has to be positive and striving
when doing things.

387
00:19:32,460 --> 00:19:33,380
Right?

388
00:19:35,740 --> 00:19:36,660
But

389
00:19:37,740 --> 00:19:38,900
if there truly is

390
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:40,260
some force majeure

391
00:19:40,260 --> 00:19:41,180
causing us

392
00:19:41,460 --> 00:19:42,500
to really not be able to return,

393
00:19:42,780 --> 00:19:45,820
if I could enter
a Culinary Master Competition

394
00:19:45,820 --> 00:19:46,820
and get a title

395
00:19:46,820 --> 00:19:48,380
of Top Chef of Yong'an,

396
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:51,140
that would be quite good.

397
00:19:51,140 --> 00:19:52,620
Top Chef of Yong'an?

398
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:04,580
So...

399
00:20:04,580 --> 00:20:05,980
none of you wants to go back anymore?

400
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:09,220
Jicai,

401
00:20:09,460 --> 00:20:10,620
all these years,

402
00:20:10,620 --> 00:20:11,900
your father hasn't brought

403
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:13,220
much money back home.

404
00:20:13,460 --> 00:20:14,700
Our whole family

405
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:16,140
has had it quite tough.

406
00:20:16,460 --> 00:20:18,500
If we can really stay in Yong'an,

407
00:20:18,700 --> 00:20:19,620
at the very least,

408
00:20:19,620 --> 00:20:21,660
our whole family will have
financial security.

409
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:26,980
- It makes sense.
- It makes sense.

410
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:41,380
(Yunshui Manor)

411
00:20:41,380 --> 00:20:42,540
Food is served!

412
00:20:44,580 --> 00:20:45,500
Vice Prefect.

413
00:20:49,620 --> 00:20:50,700
Round and Reunion.

414
00:20:51,260 --> 00:20:52,180
Reunion soon.

415
00:20:53,100 --> 00:20:55,140
Take your time.

416
00:20:59,740 --> 00:21:00,820
Fresh Reunion.

417
00:21:01,420 --> 00:21:02,620
Sweet Reunion.

418
00:21:02,620 --> 00:21:03,540
Eat.

419
00:21:06,280 --> 00:21:07,200
Grand Reunion.

420
00:21:07,300 --> 00:21:08,180
Small Reunion.

421
00:21:08,180 --> 00:21:09,100
Take your time.

422
00:21:09,660 --> 00:21:10,540
Finally Reunited.

423
00:21:10,540 --> 00:21:11,660
Never to Part.

424
00:21:15,780 --> 00:21:17,420
Uncle, you've been too generous.

425
00:21:17,420 --> 00:21:18,300
Vice Prefect,

426
00:21:18,300 --> 00:21:19,540
after you finish eating,

427
00:21:19,700 --> 00:21:21,900
I have another presumptuous request.

428
00:21:23,860 --> 00:21:25,180
Uncle, what do you want?

429
00:21:25,460 --> 00:21:26,420
Feel free to speak.

430
00:21:26,420 --> 00:21:27,340
Alright.

431
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:29,820
I...

432
00:21:29,820 --> 00:21:30,740
This...

433
00:21:30,940 --> 00:21:31,860
Actually...

434
00:21:33,860 --> 00:21:35,380
It's better for Shaojie to tell you.

435
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:44,020
Wait a moment.

436
00:21:50,740 --> 00:21:51,660
Please enjoy.

437
00:21:56,060 --> 00:21:56,980
Shen,

438
00:21:57,980 --> 00:21:58,900
you speak.

439
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:00,180
Actually, we want to...

440
00:22:02,420 --> 00:22:03,340
It's just...

441
00:22:07,020 --> 00:22:07,860
Forget it.

442
00:22:07,860 --> 00:22:09,100
Just consider me sleepwalking.

443
00:22:20,820 --> 00:22:21,740
Vice Prefect,

444
00:22:22,120 --> 00:22:23,400
we have something to tell you.

445
00:22:23,670 --> 00:22:25,140
We have something to tell you.

446
00:22:25,140 --> 00:22:26,220
Speak freely.

447
00:22:29,520 --> 00:22:30,660
Vice Prefect, are you hungry?

448
00:22:30,660 --> 00:22:32,180
I'll go make you some more food.

449
00:22:33,340 --> 00:22:34,420
This looks sufficient

450
00:22:34,820 --> 00:22:35,780
for me.

451
00:22:36,100 --> 00:22:37,020
Yes.

452
00:22:37,580 --> 00:22:38,420
Then...

453
00:22:38,420 --> 00:22:39,540
Vice Prefect, take your time.

454
00:22:41,220 --> 00:22:42,900
What could be so difficult?

455
00:22:43,300 --> 00:22:44,220
It couldn't be

456
00:22:44,220 --> 00:22:45,080
you said you were leaving,

457
00:22:45,080 --> 00:22:46,510
and now you're saying
you want to come back

458
00:22:46,510 --> 00:22:47,580
and keep living at Yunshui Manor?

459
00:22:53,940 --> 00:22:54,860
I...

460
00:22:57,100 --> 00:22:58,220
I guessed it right?

461
00:22:59,020 --> 00:22:59,940
Actually,

462
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:02,220
we have indeed encountered
some circumstances.

463
00:23:02,860 --> 00:23:04,140
We might not be able

464
00:23:04,140 --> 00:23:05,340
to leave for the time being.

465
00:23:06,260 --> 00:23:08,060
We're truly sorry, Vice Prefect.

466
00:23:08,060 --> 00:23:09,180
We can't find a place

467
00:23:09,180 --> 00:23:10,540
to go immediately.

468
00:23:10,540 --> 00:23:12,940
So, for now, we can only
stay temporarily at your place.

469
00:23:13,330 --> 00:23:14,700
Of course, we've also
thought it through.

470
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:15,630
We've earned quite a bit

471
00:23:15,630 --> 00:23:16,930
of money recently from our stall, right?

472
00:23:16,930 --> 00:23:17,900
We plan to rent a shop

473
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:18,830
and open a restaurant.

474
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:20,300
Then we can earn even more money.

475
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:21,940
In that way, we don't live
at your place in vain.

476
00:23:21,940 --> 00:23:22,940
We'll pay rent.

477
00:23:22,940 --> 00:23:24,140
What do you think?

478
00:23:31,540 --> 00:23:33,060
Renting Vice Prefect's home...

479
00:23:33,620 --> 00:23:34,900
If that word gets out,

480
00:23:34,900 --> 00:23:36,140
it would sound like I'm accusing

481
00:23:36,140 --> 00:23:38,020
His Majesty of an inadequate salary.

482
00:23:38,460 --> 00:23:39,380
This...

483
00:23:44,260 --> 00:23:45,180
Take it back.

484
00:23:47,220 --> 00:23:48,140
Stay.

485
00:23:48,460 --> 00:23:49,540
When you have time,

486
00:23:49,540 --> 00:23:51,100
just make me a portion of rice tofu.

487
00:23:52,620 --> 00:23:53,700
Rest assured!

488
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,060
Vice Prefect, from now on,

489
00:23:55,060 --> 00:23:56,260
your meals are all on us.

490
00:23:58,580 --> 00:23:59,620
You two!

491
00:24:10,340 --> 00:24:11,740
Thank you, Vice Prefect.

492
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:18,660
Knowing the Shen family isn't leaving

493
00:24:18,660 --> 00:24:19,940
puts your mind at ease, right?

494
00:24:20,340 --> 00:24:21,260
No.

495
00:24:22,020 --> 00:24:22,940
No?

496
00:24:23,450 --> 00:24:25,260
Young Master, you just got
all clumsy walking.

497
00:24:26,860 --> 00:24:27,780
I...

498
00:24:29,980 --> 00:24:31,700
I just walked all clumsy myself?

499
00:24:35,220 --> 00:24:36,540
Why are you hiding so far away?

500
00:24:36,540 --> 00:24:37,820
If I didn't hide this far,

501
00:24:37,820 --> 00:24:39,120
I'd be waiting for you to deal with me.

502
00:24:39,340 --> 00:24:40,260
How could I?

503
00:24:40,740 --> 00:24:42,620
We came out of the Cui family together.

504
00:24:42,860 --> 00:24:44,700
You are the best brother
I've had in my life.

505
00:24:44,700 --> 00:24:46,700
How could I hold a grudge

506
00:24:47,020 --> 00:24:47,980
over a joke?

507
00:24:48,260 --> 00:24:49,260
I wouldn't.

508
00:24:49,260 --> 00:24:50,220
Really?

509
00:24:54,540 --> 00:24:56,380
You still say I'm your best brother?

510
00:24:56,540 --> 00:24:57,460
You liar!

511
00:24:58,300 --> 00:24:59,220
I'm truly not lying

512
00:24:59,740 --> 00:25:00,660
to you.

513
00:25:01,020 --> 00:25:02,620
You really are my best brother

514
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:04,410
in this life.

515
00:25:06,020 --> 00:25:07,020
Again?

516
00:25:07,020 --> 00:25:08,420
You've used this trick
since we were kids.

517
00:25:08,420 --> 00:25:09,720
I've been guarding against you for ages.

518
00:25:09,900 --> 00:25:10,820
You've improved.

519
00:25:11,330 --> 00:25:12,180
However,

520
00:25:12,180 --> 00:25:14,140
I haven't seen you like this
for many years.

521
00:25:14,620 --> 00:25:16,180
Since the Shen family arrived,

522
00:25:16,180 --> 00:25:17,620
you have actually
become much more relaxed.

523
00:25:19,700 --> 00:25:20,980
But this marriage

524
00:25:21,260 --> 00:25:22,540
still has to be canceled.

525
00:25:23,300 --> 00:25:24,500
Censor Pei has no ill intent.

526
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:25,940
If he finds out, he won't spread it.

527
00:25:26,260 --> 00:25:27,540
But if it were someone else,

528
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:30,300
tracing things back
through the Shen family,

529
00:25:30,660 --> 00:25:32,540
your identity would be in danger.

530
00:26:25,060 --> 00:26:25,980
Vice Prefect,

531
00:26:26,580 --> 00:26:27,460
it's so late.

532
00:26:27,460 --> 00:26:28,580
You're not resting yet?

533
00:26:30,150 --> 00:26:31,340
There are still documents to review.

534
00:26:36,060 --> 00:26:36,980
What's wrong?

535
00:26:37,900 --> 00:26:38,900
Nothing.

536
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:41,420
It's just that I've had trouble
sleeping these past few days.

537
00:26:43,260 --> 00:26:44,620
Vice Prefect, you go back first.

538
00:26:44,620 --> 00:26:47,100
I'll sit in the courtyard for a while
and then go back.

539
00:27:23,460 --> 00:27:24,740
If there's any difficulty,

540
00:27:25,180 --> 00:27:26,940
after all, I'm the Vice Prefect.

541
00:27:27,940 --> 00:27:29,060
Perhaps I can help you.

542
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:39,660
Thank you.

543
00:27:40,300 --> 00:27:41,420
I'm really fine.

544
00:27:42,380 --> 00:27:43,460
I'll head back first.

545
00:28:12,940 --> 00:28:14,020
(Juxian Alley)
Come here.

546
00:28:14,020 --> 00:28:15,100
This way, please.

547
00:28:15,580 --> 00:28:16,980
Look! How lively.

548
00:28:17,220 --> 00:28:18,140
Yes.

549
00:28:21,420 --> 00:28:22,660
Look, so many delicious things.

550
00:28:22,660 --> 00:28:23,580
Indeed.

551
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:27,000
They say the best delicacies
in the world are in Yong'an,

552
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:28,680
and the best dishes of Yong'an
are in Juxian Alley.

553
00:28:28,680 --> 00:28:30,220
If you all want to open an eatery,

554
00:28:30,220 --> 00:28:32,140
here is truly the right place.

555
00:28:33,220 --> 00:28:34,500
Look. Up ahead are

556
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:37,300
the two most famous restaurants
in Juxian Alley.

557
00:28:37,660 --> 00:28:38,540
The first one is

558
00:28:38,540 --> 00:28:39,740
Yunlai Tavern,

559
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:40,890
the most luxurious restaurant

560
00:28:40,890 --> 00:28:42,500
in all of Yong'an.

561
00:28:42,740 --> 00:28:44,420
It caters to high officials and nobles.

562
00:28:44,420 --> 00:28:46,220
Whatever exotic delicacies
you desire to eat,

563
00:28:46,220 --> 00:28:47,740
you can taste them here.

564
00:28:50,900 --> 00:28:52,500
Look. The second one is

565
00:28:52,500 --> 00:28:53,740
Guixiang Tavern.

566
00:28:54,020 --> 00:28:55,880
(Guixiang Tavern)
Three Liu generations are running it.

567
00:28:55,940 --> 00:28:57,900
Now it's managed by Liu Feng,
Third Master Liu.

568
00:28:57,900 --> 00:29:00,420
- They emphasize elegance.
- How do you like this piece I wrote?

569
00:29:00,420 --> 00:29:02,500
- Scholars love to dine here.
- Excellent.

